The President sends his best wishes to the United States Marine Corps on its 244th birthday. He praises the Marines for their faithfulness in defending the country and Constitution and for striking fear in America's adversaries. The President also mentions the upcoming 75th anniversary of the battle of Iwo Jima, highlighting the courage and determination of the Marines. He remembers the Marines who sacrificed their lives in defense of freedom and acknowledges their toughness, leadership, and allegiance as valuable assets to the nation. The President and Melania pray for the well-being of the Armed Forces and their families, and for continued blessings upon the United States of America. The statement ends with the Marine Corps' motto, "Semper Fidelis" (Always Faithful).